feat: onAt/offAt method to switch on/off the light at a given hour/minute

// switch on the light at a given hour
onAt(pHours, pMinutes, pRepeat = false)

// switch off the light at a given hour
offAt(pHours, pMinutes, pRepeat = false)

This closes #9

feat: runMethodAt to run a given method at a given hour/minute

// run a method at hours:minutes
// hours: int
// minutes: int
// repeat: true (repeat the next day) | false (do not repeat)
runMethodAt(pMethod, pHours, pMinutes, pRepeat = false)

This closes #8

feat: Add _sendMessage method

In Avantek class we need to be able to send a message to the light.

This method must take an object as argument and this object will be concat to _baseRequest attribute.

For example:

this._baseRequest = {
   uid: `0`,
   sid: `theSid`
};
and

let msg = {
   cmd: 'switch',
   arg: {
      on: 1
   }
}
Should send this message :

{
   uid: `0`,
   sid: `theSid`,
   cmd: 'switch',
   arg: {
      on: 1
   }
}

This closes #1
